l aspects of a trial from a Freudian viewpoint; one political scientist, Peter Russell, examine the courts' role in the development of the law; another, Donald Smiley, studies their role as protector of civil liberties; James Giffen, a sociologist, points out the inadequacy of the criminal justice system as a means of controlling alcohol and drug addiction; Donald Dewees, an economist, examines court regulation of economic behaviour; and Kenneth McNaught, a historian, discusses the political trial in the Canadian legal system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCourtszCanada. 0aJudicial processzCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Reginald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDewees, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoob, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedland, Martin L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGiffen, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanly, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcnaught, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRapoport, Anatol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRussell, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmiley, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148759557940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487595579423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487595579.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archi